    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen doing search/replace the user is presented with a \"cryptic\" help in the form of \n` (y/n/a/q/l/^E/^Y)`\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI propose we elaborate a bit on the help text to cater for the inexperienced by explaining each option, for example \n` (y)es/(n)o/(a)ll/(q) stop/(l) replace and stop/(^E) scroll down/(^Y) scroll up` \n\nor if this is too verbose we could skip the readily understandable ones (y/n/a/q)\n` (y/n/a/q/l (replace+stop)/^E (down)/^Y (up)) ` \n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
